## Automatic Workflow Detection

Workflows activate via natural-language keywords â€” no `/command` required.
The `UserPromptSubmit` hook detects keywords and injects `[OMA WORKFLOW: ...]` into context.
Trigger keywords are defined in `.claude/hooks/triggers.json` (multi-language support).

### Hook Behavior
- `[OMA WORKFLOW: ...]` â†’ read and execute the workflow file immediately
- `[OMA PERSISTENT MODE: ...]` â†’ workflow still in progress, continue execution
- Informational context ("what is X?") is filtered out â€” no false triggers
- Explicit `/command` input skips the hook (no duplication)
- Persistent-mode workflows (`ultrawork`, `orchestrate`, `work`) block termination until complete
- Deactivate persistent mode: say "workflow done" â†’ deletes `.agents/state/{workflow}-state-{sessionId}.json`

